DEVELOPING.md now states the maintainer release policy explicitly:
- `main` is latest integrated, not the stable boundary
- stable releases are non-prerelease tags on `main`
- prereleases are `-rc` / `-beta` tags on `main`
- no separate `stable` branch at this stage unless backports become real

This keeps maintainer policy concrete without leaking it into user-facing product surfaces beyond the necessary README install guidance.
